riti Pratishtan]], New Delhi<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thehindu.com/2003/11/28/stories/2003112808050400.htm|title=The Hindu : Sanskriti Awards announced|website=The Hindu}}</ref>\n* 2012 \u2013 [[Kerala Sangeetha Nataka Akademi|Kerala Sangeetha Nataka]] Award for Theatre Direction<ref>{{cite web|url=http://keralatheatre.blogspot.com/2013/02/kerala-sangeetha-nataka-akademi-award.html|title=Kerala Sangeetha Nataka Akademi Award for Abhilash Pillai}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.keralaculture.org/|title=Drama, Awards, Kerala Sangeetha Nataka Akademi|website=keralaculture.org}}</ref>\n* 2012 \u2013 [[Vayala Vasudevan Pillai]] Award for overall contribution to theatre.\n* 2013 \u2013 Rangkarmee Ram Vinay Rang Samman from Ashirwad Rangmandal, Begusarai, Bihar.\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Abhilash Pillai}}\n[[Category:Indian theatre directors]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Theatre practitioners]]\n[[Category:Indian drama teachers]]\n[[Category:National School of Drama alumni]]\n[[Category:1969 births]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Director (b. 1969)}}\n{{Use Indian English|date= February 2019}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2020}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name = Abhilash Pillai\n| image = Dr Abhilash Pillai pic.jpg\n| caption =\n| birth_name = Abhilash Pillai\n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|1969|05|17|df=y}}\n| native_name_lang = ml\n| birth_place = [[Thiruvanathapuram]], [[Kerala]]\n| alma_mater = [[National School of Drama]], [[Royal Academy of Dramatic Art]]\n| occupation = [[Theatre director]], [[Scenographer]], [[Academic]]\n| website =\n}}\n\n'''Abhilash Pillai''' (born 17 May 1969) is an Indian [[Theatre|theater]] director, both [[Pedagogy|pedagogue]] and scholar of contemporary [[Theatre of India|Indian theatre]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://indianexpress.com/article/lifestyle/art-and-culture/theatre-nsd-abhilash-pillai-delhi-art-5552982/|title=Director Abhilash Pillai on exploring the mind of an artist in Blindside|date=24 January 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thehindu.com/features/friday-review/theatre/new-act-on-stage/article2697578.ece|title=New act on stage|last=Paul|first=G. S.|date=8 December 2011|via=www.thehindu.com}}</ref>\n\n==Early life and education==\nAbhilash Pillai was born on 17 May 1969 at [[Thiruvananthapuram]] to S.R.K. Pillai and Sarada Pillai. In 1991, he completed his Bachelor of Theatre Arts from The School of Drama, [[University of Calicut]] and secured third rank. He also completed a three-year Postgraduate Diploma in Dramatics with a specialization in Design and Direction from the [[National School of Drama]] (NSD), [[New Delhi]], with distinction in 1994. He then obtained a two-year Diploma in Theater Production and Stage Management with honors from the [[Royal Academy of Dramatic Art]] (RADA), [[London]] in 1998. He also did a one-year intensive training in advanced theater direction in association with eminent directors in the [[Orange Tree Theatre|Orange Tree Theater]], United Kingdom during 1998 and 1999 and attained his PhD from [[Jawaharlal Nehru University]], [[New Delhi]] in 2012.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://theatrefestivalkerala.com/cgi-sys/suspendedpage.cgi|title=Account Suspended|website=theatrefestivalkerala.com}}</ref>\n\n==Career==\nDr. Pillai began his career in theater as an [[art director]] at the Abhinaya Theatre and Research Centre, [[Thiruvananthapuram]] in [[Kerala]]. He worked there from September 1999 to April 2001. Later, he was appointed as an Assistant Professor at [[National School of Drama]], New Delhi and rose to become the Dean of Academics from July 2008 and June 2011. Presently, he is a visiting faculty/play director at many universities in [[India]] and abroad. He is also the Chairman of Arnav Art Trust since 2011 and a committee member of ''Natrang Pratishtan'', [[New Delhi]]. He currently works as the Associate Professor at [[National School of Drama]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thehindu.com/features/friday-review/theatre/abhilash-pillais-play-lorem-ipsum-review/article7232011.ece|title=Destination unknown|first=Diwan Singh|last=Bajeli|date=21 May 2015|via=www.thehindu.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://collegedunia.com/college/5510-national-school-of-drama-nsd-new-delhi|title=National School of Drama \u2013 [NSD], New Delhi|website=Collegedunia}}</ref>\n\n== Major directorial works ==\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|- \"\n! Year !! Title !! [[Dramaturge]] !! Production Company !! Premier Show\n|-\n| 2017||''The Night Side of Life''|| Sasikumar. V || Ex-Theatre Asia || [[National Theater and Concert Hall, Taipei]], [[Taiwan]] \n|-\n| 2016||''Talatum''|| Sasikumar. V || Tempest with a Twist by Sasikumar. V combining Theatre actors & circus performers in a circus tent ||  Serendipity Art Trust,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.livemint.com/Leisure/yXPVL1s6DhFInAsqyjrffL/Lounge-loves-A-multidisciplinary-Tempest-from-Kerala.html|title=Lounge loves: A multi-disciplinary 'Tempest' from Kerala|first=Avantika|last=Bhuyan|date=18 November 2016|website=Mint}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thehindu.com/entertainment/theatre/A-tent-filled-with-Shakespeare%E2%80%99s-magic/article16907310.ece|title=A tent filled with Shakespeare\u2019s magic|first=Vikram|last=Phukan|date=20 December 2016|via=www.thehindu.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://digitalgoa.com/theatre-finds-a-new-way-of-expression-through-talatum-a-contemporary-adaptation-of-shakespeares-tempest/|title=Theatre finds a new way of expression through Talatum: A Contemporary adaptation of Shakespeare\u2019s Tempest \u2013 Digital Goa|first=Team Digital|last=Goa}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/goa/Shakespeares-Tempest-to-get-a-circus-style-makeover/articleshow/56073862.cms|title=Shakespeare\u2019s Tempest to get a circus-style makeover \u2013 Times of India|website=The Times of India}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2016||''Radio Freedom''||[[Rajesh Taila