  || \n|- \n| 1990||''Subhala Vajra Thundam''||Malayalam translation from Sanskrit (Children's play) by Srirama adapted by P.G. Unnikrishnan ||  || \n|- \n| 1989||''Oru Kootam Urumpukal, (A group of Ants) Children's play''||[[G. Sankara Pillai]] ||  || \n|}\n\n==As an Actor==\n*1987 \u2013 Indrajith in Lanka Lakshmi of [[C. N. Sreekantan Nair|C.N. Sreekantan Nair]], directed by Krishnan Namboodiri\n*1988 \u2013 Carpenter in Andorra authored by [[Max Frisch]], directed by Ashoken, Thrissur School of Drama\n*1988 \u2013 Common-man in Mahendra Varman's Mathavilasam directed by [[Kavalam Narayana Panicker|Kavalam Narayana Panikke]]<nowiki/>r, Kerala\n*1989 \u2013 Curtain-holder in Pancharatra of [[Bh\u0101sa|Bhasa]], under the direction of [[B. V. Karanth|B.V. Karanth]]\n*1990 \u2013 Third Son in Bhasa's [[Madhyamavyayoga|Madhyama Vyayoga]], directed by Rajendren Thayattu\n\n==Awards==\n* 2003 \u2013 National Sanskriti Award 2002\u201303 (National Cultural Award) for achievements in theatre in December 2003 by [[Sanskriti Pratishthan|Sanskriti Pratishtan]], New Delhi<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thehindu.com/2003/11/28/stories/2003112808050400.htm|title=The Hindu : Sanskriti Awards announced|website=The Hindu}}</ref>\n* 2012 \u2013 [[Kerala Sangeetha Nataka Akademi|Kerala Sangeetha Nataka]] Award for Theatre Direction<ref>{{cite web|url=http://keralatheatre.blogspot.com/2013/02/kerala-sangeetha-nataka-akademi-award.html|title=Kerala Sangeetha Nataka Akademi Award for Abhilash Pillai}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.keralaculture.org/|title=Drama, Awards, Kerala Sangeetha Nataka Akademi|website=keralaculture.org}}</ref>\n* 2012 \u2013 [[Vayala Vasudevan Pillai]] Award for overall contribution to theatre.\n* 2013 \u2013 Rangkarmee Ram Vinay Rang Samman from Ashirwad Rangmandal, Begusarai, Bihar.\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Abhilash Pillai}}\n[[Category:Indian theatre directors]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Theatre practitioners]]\n