lvida'', starring [[Milind Soman]], [[Gul Panag]] and [[Waheeda Rahman]]. In 2006, he made his debut as a director with ''[[Sacred Evil \u2013 A True Story]]''.<ref name=Glamsham/> He produced TV series, ''[[Kaali \u2013 Ek Agnipariksha]]'', which was aired on [[Star Plus]]<ref>{{cite news |title=Star plus show 'Kaali-Ek Agnipariksha' ends on a high note |url=https://news.webindia123.com/news/articles/India/20110319/1712399.html |publisher=Webindia123 |date=March 19, 2011}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Pillai |first1=Pooja |title=Split screen |url=http://archive.indianexpress.com/news/split-screen/726887/ |publisher=[[Indian Express]] |date=December 20, 2010}}</ref> In 2009, Abhigyan Jha launched [[Jay Hind!]], a [[standup comedy]] show exclusively for the [[Internet]] platform. It was the world's first full format TV show exclusively  made for the [[Internet]].<ref name=telegraph>{{cite news |last1=Roy |first1=Priyanka |title=Jai ho to Jay Hind! |url=https://www.telegraphindia.com/entertainment/jai-ho-to-jay-hind/cid/527344 |publisher=[[Telegraph India]] |date=April 27, 2010}}</ref> He is credited for pioneering the [[standup comedy]] genre in India on TV with [[Varun Grover (writer)|Varun Grover]], [[Aditi Mittal]], [[Sorabh Pant]], [[Gursimran Khamba]] and [[Sapan Verma]].<ref>{{cite news |last1=Jaisinghani |first1=Bella |title=Spoof on India's highest civilian awards |url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/mumbai/Spoof-on-Indias-highest-civilian-awards/articleshow/20891427.cms |publisher=[[The Times of India]] |date=July 3, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Deo |first1=Sumedha |title=Indian awards: for better or for worse |url=https://www.hindustantimes.com/entertainment/indian-awards-for-better-or-for-worse/story-83spNwtcrF2ehibLKRzd1H.html |publisher=[[Hindustan Times]] |date=July 4, 2013}}</ref>\n\nAbhigyan was nominated for [[ITA Award|ITA Award for Best Director]] - Comedy at the [[Indian Television Academy Awards]] 2011 for ''[[Jay Hind!]]''.<ref>{