58]]\n* [[Avro RJ100]]\n* [[Boeing 717]]\n* [[Boeing 737 Next Generation|Boeing 737-600]]\n* [[Bombardier CRJ700 series]]\n* [[Embraer E-Jet family|Embraer 195]]\n* [[Fokker 100]]\n* [[Sukhoi Superjet 100]]\n* [[Tupolev Tu-334]]\n* [[Yakovlev Yak-42]]\n|lists=\n* [[List of Airbus A320 operators]]\n* [[List of jet airliners]]\n* [[Lists of airlines]]\n|see also=\n* [[Airbus Corporate Jets]]\n}}\n\n==References==\n;Footnotes\n{{notelist}}\n\n;References\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n;Bibliography\n* \"World Airliner Census\". ''Flight International'', Volume 184, Number 5403, 13\u201319 August 2013, pp.&nbsp;40\u201358.\n* {{Cite book|last=Gunston|first=Bill|authorlink=Bill Gunston|title=Airbus: The Complete Story|year=2009|location=Sparkford, Yeovil, Somerset, UK |publisher=Haynes Publishing|isbn=978-1-84425-585-6|ref={{harvid|Gunston|2009}}}}\n* {{Cite book|last1=Norris|first1=Guy and Mark Wagner|title=Airbus|location=Osceola, Wisconsin|publisher=MBI Publishing|year=1999|isbn=978-0-7603-0677-2|ref={{harvid|Norris|Wagner|1999}}|url-access=registration|url=https://archive.org/details/airbus0000norr}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category|Airbus A318}}\n* [http://www.airbus.com/en/aircraftfamilies/a320/ Official Airbus website of the A320 aircraft family]\n\n{{Airbus A3xx timeline}}\n{{airbus aircraft}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Airbus A318}}\n[[Category:Airbus aircraft|A318]]\n[[Category:2000s international airliners]]\n[[Category:Twinjets]]\n[[Category:Airbus A320 family]]\n", "name_user": "Skyring", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eSpecifications", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Airbus_A318"}
{"title_page": "Abd\u00fclhamit Bilici", "text_new": "{{Infobox person\n| name        = Abd\u00fclhamit Bilici\n| image       = \n| alt         = \n| caption     = \n| birth_name  = \n| birth_date  = \n| death_date  = \n| death_place = \n| residence   = [[Istanbul]]\n| nationality = Turkish\n| other_names = Twitter: @ahamitbilici\n| alma_mater  = [[Bo\u011fazi\u00e7i University]]\n| occupation  = Journalist, Writer\n| years_active = \n| website     = {{URL|http://cihan.com.tr/}}\n}}\n\n'''Abd\u00fclhamit Bilici''' (born 1970 in [[Erzurum]]) is a [[Turkey|Turkish]] newspaper executive and, since 2015, the editor-in-chief of the newspaper ''[[Zaman (newspaper)|Zaman]]''. He is also the Chief Executive Officer of its English-language version, ''[[Today's Zaman]]''. He was  general director of [[Cihan News Agency]] and editor of ''[[Aksiyon]] Weekly Magazine''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.aksiyon.com.tr/aksiyon/haber-3520-36-oglumu-onlara-teslim-ettim.html |title=Aksiyon |publisher=aksiyon.com.tr |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140717001419/http://www.aksiyon.com.tr/aksiyon/haber-3520-36-oglumu-onlara-teslim-ettim.html |archivedate=2014-07-17 }}</ref>\n\nHe speaks English. Bilici is married and has two children.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=GRh82_wGRII |title= Inside Story - Syria's civil war - al jazeera English - Abd\u00fclhamit Bilici|publisher=youtube.com}}</ref>\n\n==Early life==\nBilici attending primary school education in [[\u0130stanbul]] and graduated from high school in [[Erzurum]]. He read for a BA in Political Sciences and International Relations Department at [[Bo\u011fazi\u00e7i University|Bosporus University]] in 1993. He obtained a master's degree from Department of Economics at [[Istanbul University]] with a thesis titled \u201c''Energy Structure of Turkmenistan and Natural Gas''\u201d. He is currently a doctoral student at Department of International Relations at the same university. Bilici also has MBA degree from Faculty of Management at [[Fatih University]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=XqDwCk87UMM |title= Habert\u00fcrk 13 Mart 2014 - Abd\u00fclhamit Bilici|publisher=youtube.com}}</ref>\n\n==Career==\nStarting his career at ''Zaman'' as a correspondent, Bilici worked as an editor at ''Aksiyon'' between 1995-1997, as foreign news editor at ''Zaman'' between 1998-2001, as general editor at Zaman Daily between 2002-2008 and as general director of Cihan News Agency and as the editor-in-chief of the newspaper ''Zaman Newspaper.'' He is a columnist for Zaman and ''Today's Zaman'' dailies.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.salihsarikaya.com/darbe-zihniyetinden-kurtulmak-icin-abyi-istiyoruz/ |title=Abant Platformu 2. g\u00fcn\u00fcnde AB s\u00fcrecini konu\u015ftu: Darbe zihniyetinden kurtulmak i\u00e7in AB\u2019yi istiyoruz |publisher=salihsarikaya.com |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140719145907/http://www.salihsarikaya.com/darbe-zihniyetinden-kurtulmak-icin-abyi-istiyoruz/ |archivedate=2014-07-19 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://cihan.com.tr/bottomMenu?linkid=identity |title=Cihan Haber Ajans\u0131 K\u00fcnye |publisher=Cihan.com.tr |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140704034423/http://www.cihan.com.tr/bottomMenu?linkid=identity |archivedate=2014-07-04 }}</ref> He writes mainly on Turkish foreign policy and world politics. He is a frequent commentator on local and international television programs.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=79oqxPaUZrw |title= 23 Aral\u0131k 2013 Sky News Sky News Abd\u00fclhamit Bilici |publisher=youtube.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=7XsmYawUZnw |title= Syria's civil war? - Abd\u00fclhamit Bilici |publisher=youtube.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=3Yqs7yeoK2w |title= 7 Mart 2014 CNN TURK - KAR\u015eI G\u00dcNDEM - Abd\u00fclhamit Bilici|publisher=youtube.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=NZ8Yhbq8UTA |title= 13 Mart Bugun TV G\u00fcne Baki\u015f Abd\u00fclhamit Bilici |publisher=youtube.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.volkskrant.nl/buitenland/article476174.ece/Kemal_Ataturk_zou_zich_misbruikt_voelen |title= Dutch daily Volkskrant interview Bilici on tension in Turkish politics |publisher=youtube.com}}</ref>\n\n==Bibliography==\nBilici edited a book titled \u201cWhy Turkey?\u201d which combines different perspectives on Turkey-EU relations from both sides.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.pandora.com.tr/urun/neden-turkiye-why-turkey/136809 |title=Neden T\u00fcrkiye - Why Turkey}}</ref>\n\nBilici is a member of the [[Turkish Journalists' Association|Turkish Journalists Association]] (TGC), Journalists and Writers Foundation (GYV) and [[World Association of Newspapers and News Publishers|World Association of Newspapers]] (WAN).<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.gyv.org.tr/ |title=GYV.com.tr |publisher=gyv.com.tr |access-date=2014-07-15 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140717073812/http://www.gyv.org.tr/ |archive-date=2014-07-17 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\n== Some of his columns published at Today\u2019s Zaman ==\n* Genes of Turkish media, clich\u00e9s of the West [https://web.archive.org/web/20160305080004/http://www.todayszaman.com/columnists/abdulhamit-bilici_246155-genes-of-turkish-media-clich-s-of-the-west.html]\n* What if Soma disaster had been in South Korea? [https://web.archive.org/web/20140717031713/http://www.todayszaman.com/columnist/abdulhamit-bilici_349174_what-if-soma-disaster-had-been-in-south-korea.html]\n* Turkey's two new impasses [https://web.archive.org/web/20140509150324/http://www.todayszaman.com/columnist/abdulhamit-bilici_329178_turkeys-two-new-impasses.html]\n* Normalization with Armenian surrealism? [https://web.archive.org/web/20160305000840/http://www.todayszaman.com/columnists/abdulhamit-bilici_207650-normalization-with-armenian-surrealism.html]\n* Is Turkey detaching itself or is the West excluding it? [https://web.archive.org/web/20140714141324/http://www.todayszaman.com/columnists/abdulhamit-bilici_204188-is-turkey-detaching-itself-or-is-the-west-excluding-it.html]\n* What is the military's place? [https://web.archive.org/web/20160305003909/http://www.todayszaman.com/columnists/abdulhamit-bilici_197455-what-is-the-militarys-place.html]\n\n== Some of his columns published at Zaman Daily ==\n* Soma, G\u00fcney Kore\u2019de olsayd\u0131! [https://web.archive.org/web/20140714164848/http://www.zaman.com.tr/abdulhamit-bilici/soma-guney-korede-olsaydi_2218782.html]\n* \u015eimdi Hasan Cemal de New York Times da k\u00f6t\u00fc oldu! [https://web.archive.org/web/20140714182238/http://www.zaman.com.tr/full-name/simdi-hasan-cemal-de-new-york-times-da-kotu-oldu_2197514.html]\n* D\u0131\u015f politika karnesi! [https://web.archive.org/web/20140714180349/http://www.zaman.com.tr/full-name/dis-politika-karnesi_2178878.html]\n\n== Some of TV programs and live broadcast he attended ==\n* [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=XqDwCk87UMM Habert\u00fcrk 13 Mart 2014 - Abd\u00fclhamit Bilici]\n* [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=3Yqs7yeoK2w 7 Mart 2014 CNN TURK - KAR\u015eI G\u00dcNDEM - Abd\u00fclhamit Bilici ]\n* [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=NZ8Yhbq8UTA 13 Mart Bugun TV G\u00fcne Baki\u015f Abd\u00fclhamit Bilici ]\n* [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=79oqxPaUZrw 23 Aral\u0131k 2013 Sky News Sky News Abd\u00fclhamit Bilici ]\n* [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=qDc5BX_QMIg SamanyoluHaber Abdulhamit Bilici -03 Nisan 2014 - Yerel se\u00e7im sonras\u0131 K\u00f6\u015fk se\u00e7im seneryolar\u0131 ]\n* [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=7XsmYawUZnw Syria's civil war?]\n* [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=LEXXCdH2nqc CNN TURK, Cihan Haber Ajans\u0131 2014 se\u00e7im \u00e7al\u0131\u015fmalar\u0131 ]\n* Dutch daily Volkskrant interview Bilici on tension in Turkish politics: [http://www.volkskrant.nl/buitenland/article476174.ece/Kemal_Ataturk_zou_zich_misbruikt_voelen]\n\